---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import typescript from '../../../benchmarks/compilers/typescript-baseline.json';
import go from '../../../benchmarks/compilers/go.json';
import rust from '../../../benchmarks/compilers/rust.json';
import zig from '../../../benchmarks/compilers/zig.json';
const rows = [
  { name: 'TypeScript', href: '/typescript/', scope: 'Full product baseline; benchmark planning workload differs', data: typescript },
  { name: 'Go', href: '/go/', scope: 'Protocol planner artifacts only', data: go },
  { name: 'Rust', href: '/rust/', scope: 'Protocol planner artifacts only', data: rust },
  { name: 'Zig', href: '/zig/', scope: 'Protocol planner artifacts only', data: zig },
];
const format = value => Number(value).toLocaleString(undefined, { maximumFractionDigits: 3 });
const relative = value => `${(value / typescript.summary.medianWallMs).toFixed(2)}× TS recorded median`;
---
<Layout title="Compiler benchmark comparison · Kumo">
  <header class="intro"><p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">Compiler candidates</a> / Comparison</p><h1>Compiler benchmark comparison</h1><p>The checked-in measurements are shown together for transparency, with scope labels that prevent unlike workloads from being treated as a race.</p></header>
  <aside class="warning"><strong>No winner is declared.</strong> Go, Rust, and Zig emit deterministic protocol planner artifacts rather than full framework source. TypeScript remains the current full product baseline and its benchmark performs a different planning workload, so these wall-clock values are not a fair winner comparison.</aside>
  <section aria-labelledby="table-title"><h2 id="table-title">Recorded measurements</h2><div class="table-scroll"><table><thead><tr><th scope="col">Candidate</th><th scope="col">Scope</th><th scope="col">Median wall</th><th scope="col">Relative metric</th><th scope="col">p95</th><th scope="col">Variance</th><th scope="col">Output</th><th scope="col">CPU / RSS</th></tr></thead><tbody>{rows.map(row => <tr><th scope="row"><a href={row.href}>{row.name}</a><small>{row.data.compiler.toolchain}</small></th><td data-label="Scope">{row.scope}</td><td data-label="Median">{format(row.data.summary.medianWallMs)} ms</td><td data-label="Relative">{relative(row.data.summary.medianWallMs)}</td><td data-label="p95">{format(row.data.summary.p95WallMs)} ms</td><td data-label="Variance">{format(row.data.summary.varianceWallMs)} ms²</td><td data-label="Output">{row.data.output.files} files<br/>{row.data.output.bytes.toLocaleString()} bytes</td><td data-label="CPU / RSS">Unavailable / unavailable</td></tr>)}</tbody></table></div></section>
  <section class="method" aria-labelledby="method-title"><h2 id="method-title">Methodology</h2><p>Every JSON record contains <strong>2 discarded warmups</strong> and <strong>10 measured samples</strong>. Each sample uses a fresh Node process and fresh output root; the first measured sample is labeled cold, and wall time includes process startup. Runs were recorded on Apple M4 Pro, arm64, macOS 25.4.0 with Node v24.17.0.</p><p>All candidates report 41 components, 164 target plans, and 164 deterministic output files. Output byte totals and hashes differ because artifact formats and workload scope differ. Portable startup, CPU, and peak RSS telemetry were not captured; zero CPU fields and null RSS fields are displayed as unavailable rather than as measured zero.</p></section>
</Layout>
<style>
.intro{max-width:850px;padding:30px 0 10px}.eyebrow{color:#64748b;font-size:12px;font-weight:750;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase}.eyebrow a{color:inherit}.intro h1{margin:8px 0;font-size:clamp(38px,5vw,58px);letter-spacing:-.045em}.intro>p:last-child{color:#475569;font-size:18px;line-height:1.65}.warning{margin:24px 0 42px;padding:17px 20px;border-left:4px solid #d97706;background:#fffbeb;color:#78350f;line-height:1.6}h2{font-size:25px}.table-scroll{overflow-x:auto;border:1px solid #d8dde5;border-radius:10px}table{width:100%;min-width:1100px;border-collapse:collapse;background:#fff}th,td{padding:13px;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;font-size:12px;font-variant-numeric:tabular-nums}thead th{background:#f7f8fa;color:#475569}tbody th a{color:#0759b6;font-size:15px}tbody th small{display:block;max-width:180px;margin-top:5px;color:#64748b;font-weight:400}.method{max-width:850px;margin:42px 0}.method p{color:#475569;line-height:1.65}@media(max-width:700px){.intro>p:last-child{font-size:16px}.table-scroll{overflow:visible;border:0}table{min-width:0}thead{position:absolute;width:1px;height:1px;overflow:hidden;clip:rect(0 0 0 0)}tbody,tr,th,td{display:block}tbody tr{margin-bottom:12px;border:1px solid #d8dde5;border-radius:9px;background:#fff}tbody th,tbody td{border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb}tbody td::before{content:attr(data-label);display:block;margin-bottom:4px;color:#64748b;font-size:10px;font-weight:750;text-transform:uppercase}}
</style>
